The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques to predict clinical interventions in ICU patients using data from various sources. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory networks (LSTM) for prediction suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories may also be relevant. Finally, the focus on clinical applications suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational biology and bioinformatics (cs.CE) sub-category.
